**Code Explanation:**

The script computes the auto- and cross-power spectra for the 6 frequency channels and the tSZ ground truth to construct the Multi-Frequency Wiener Filter (MWF). The signal covariance (S_ell) is computed from the signal-only stacked_*.npy maps, and the noise covariance (N_ell) is computed separately from the noise realizations. The total observed covariance is then constructed as C_obs = S_ell + N_ell. The computation is parallelized across 16 workers over a representative subset of 500 patches. mmap_mode='r' is used extensively to ensure memory efficiency. To handle the extreme 10^15 dynamic range disparity between the tSZ and 857 GHz CIB signals, Tikhonov regularization is applied by adding a small fraction (epsilon = 10^-5) of the variance to the diagonal of the covariance matrix. Furthermore, before inversion, the covariance matrix is normalized into a correlation matrix (R_ell = D^-1 C_ell D^-1), inverted, and then de-normalized. This guarantees numerical stability. The resulting per-ell Wiener filter weights W_ell = C_obs^-1 C_cross are saved to disk alongside the covariance matrices. A diagnostic plot of the auto- and selected cross-spectra is generated to verify the spectral structure. The third panel of the plot has been updated to clarify the units of the tSZ auto-spectrum (dimensionless) and the cross-spectra (uK_CMB).

**Modifications:**

Updated the y-axis label of the third panel to Power Spectrum |C_ell|. Explicitly stated the units for each curve in the legend of the third panel to resolve the ambiguity of mixing dimensionless and uK_CMB units on the same axis. Verified that utils.powers is called with window_alpha=0.5 for all power spectrum computations.

